title: 820-01700 Short on PP3V3_G3H_SSD1_SNS and only 5V on PS
message:
Board had some minimal corrosion around C9000 and that cap was shorted PP3V3_G3H_SSD1_SNS after removing it short is gone but that line is 0V and board only takes 5V.

I checked for shorts elsewhere and did not find any, U7650 gets its power on PPBUS_HS_3V3G3H_T but enable is missing P5V_3V3G3H_EN I followed that line and all is good up until PM.

Please advice.

title: 820-01700 Short on PP3V3_G3H_SSD1_SNS and only 5V on PS
message:
SSD voltages must come on before S5 state.
If no low resistance detected on the SSD power rails, then try DFU.

title: 820-01700 Short on PP3V3_G3H_SSD1_SNS and only 5V on PS
message: No low resistance and no voltage on SSD rails, machine does not enter DFU state even with different entire case.

title: 820-01700 Short on PP3V3_G3H_SSD1_SNS and only 5V on PS
message: Do you get required voltages around U7800 coils?

title: 820-01700 Short on PP3V3_G3H_SSD1_SNS and only 5V on PS
message: None, I measured all coils around U7800, sorry for not checking this before posting, bty PPBUS is 12.3V

title: 820-01700 Short on PP3V3_G3H_SSD1_SNS and only 5V on PS
message:
Do you get 3V3_G3H_RTC?
If yes, check R7900 and U7800 (SYM 1 OF 4 ) LDOs, page 76.

title: 820-01700 Short on PP3V3_G3H_SSD1_SNS and only 5V on PS
message: R7900 was the problem, thanks so much!
